text: Argysh () is a rural locality (a village) in Cherlakovsky Selsoviet, Dyurtyulinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 112 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 37 km from Dyurtyuli, 6 km from Cherlak. == References == Category:Rural localities in Dyurtyulinsky District
title: Argysh
